  "time_ut": 1660726624,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Jacqueline is guilty",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lankan Bollywood actress Jacqueline Fernandez has been found guilty of extorting money from an Indian.",
        "Bollywood actress Jacqueline has been named as the culprit by the Enforcement Directorate in the Rs 215 crore extortion case.",
        "The Enforcement Directorate filed a chargesheet against Bollywood actress Jacqueline Fernandez today (17).",
        "The Enforcement Directorate says that Jacqueline knew that Sukesh Chandrasekhar was an extortionist and Jacqueline was his accomplice.",
        "Earlier, ED found that Sukesh Chandrasekhar had sent gifts worth Rs 10 crore to actress Jacqueline. So far, the Enforcement Directorate has seized more than Rs 7 crore of the actress' assets under the Anti-Money Laundering Act.",
        "Jacqueline Fernandez was repeatedly investigated by the Enforcement Directorate for alleged links with Sukesh Chandrasekhar.",
        "Sukesh Chandrasekhar has 32 criminal cases against him and is being investigated by several state police and three central agencies \u2013 CBI, Enforcement Directorate and Income Tax.",
        "Sukesh Chandrasekhar was accused of extorting Rs 215 crore from the wife of a New Delhi businessman through a fake call. Due to this he was arrested by the Delhi Police.",
        "After investigating him, it was revealed that Sukesh had extorted money from the victim by pretending to be an official of the Prime Minister's Office, Ministry of Law and Ministry of Home Affairs.",
        "Apart from that, Sukesh said over the phone that he would grant bail to the victim's husband and run their drug business. Sukesh is involved in the fraud case against AAMUK leader DTV Dhinakaran. He was arrested by the Enforcement Directorate on April 4 in connection with this case."
      ],
